    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl mb-6 leading-tight">How to use ChatGPT or Claude for your own marketing</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">A beginner guide for business owners, contractors, and service providers who want to use AI in everyday work without overcomplicating it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<article class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5">
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">Artificial intelligence is no longer just for large companies. Tools like ChatGPT and Claude can help a local business write better posts, answer common questions, organize ideas, create promotions, and save time on repetitive digital marketing tasks.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Why a small business should use AI</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">If you own a business or provide a service, you probably handle many things at once: serving customers, quoting jobs, posting on social media, asking for reviews, answering messages, and thinking about how to attract more customers. AI marketing tools do not replace your experience, but they can turn your ideas into clear content faster.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">What you can do with ChatGPT or Claude</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-5">These tools work best when you give them context about your business, your customers, and your goal. You can use them to:</p>
      <ul class="checklist mb-8">
        <li>Create ideas for Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, or LinkedIn posts.</li>
        <li>Write service descriptions for your website or Google Business Profile.</li>
        <li>Prepare professional replies for messages, emails, and frequently asked questions.</li>
        <li>Turn recent job photos into captions for social media.</li>
        <li>Plan monthly promotions, seasonal offers, and local campaigns.</li>
        <li>Generate short scripts for videos, reels, or ads.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Basic prompts to get started</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-5">A prompt is the instruction you give the AI. The more specific you are, the better the response. Try examples like these:</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-100 p-6 mb-8" style="background:var(--surf)">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Social media prompt:</strong> "Act as a small business marketing expert. I have a [service] business in [city]. Give me 10 post ideas to attract local customers, with short copy, a call to action, and a professional but friendly tone."</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong>Google Business prompt:</strong> "Write an optimized Google Business Profile description for my [service] business. I want to highlight experience, trust, local service, and fast response."</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed"><strong>Promotion prompt:</strong> "Create 5 simple promotions for a [service] business this month. Include a title, social media copy, and a WhatsApp message."</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">How to add AI to your daily work</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-5">You do not need to change your whole process. Start with a simple routine:</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8 space-y-3">
        <li>On Monday, ask ChatGPT or Claude for five content ideas for the week.</li>
        <li>On Tuesday, turn a completed job photo into a before-and-after post.</li>
        <li>On Wednesday, review your common questions and create clear customer replies.</li>
        <li>On Thursday, write a short follow-up email or message for prospects.</li>
        <li>On Friday, ask what worked and what to publish next week.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">The key: review before publishing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">AI can write quickly, but you should review everything. Make sure the content sounds like your business, does not promise things you do not offer, uses correct pricing, and includes accurate local information. The best strategy combines AI, human judgment, and real customer knowledge.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-4">Where AI fits in your marketing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">ChatGPT, Claude, and other artificial intelligence tools can help with content, ideas, and organization, but marketing needs more pieces: a clear website, local SEO, an updated Google Business Profile, reviews, well-targeted ads, and follow-up with leads.</p>

      <p class="text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">If you want to use AI in a practical way, start small: create weekly content, improve your replies, and organize your promotions. Then connect that work to a complete <a href="/en/blog/internet-marketing-services-small-business/" style="color:var(--primary)">internet marketing services</a> strategy to attract more customers and measure results.</p>
    </div>
